<item>
            <title>[FELIX-5044] [DS] (felix-extensions) Service property changes during service registration get ignored</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-5044</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;felix-extensions allows event and lifecycle methods to return the new service property map.  However, there&apos;s a timing hole.  These changes are only applied when m_serviceRegistration is non-null.  Thus any changes that occur between the time the service is registered and m_serviceRegistration is set will be dropped.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will occur when service registration results in something calling getService resulting in activation before m_serviceRegistration is recorded and one of the event methods or activation trying to change the service properties.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
